#. <section class="sutta" id="sn23.8"><article><div class="hgroup"><p class="division">
msgctxt "sn23.8:0.1"
msgid "Saṃyutta Nikāya 23"
msgstr "Linked Discourses 23"

#. </p><p>
msgctxt "sn23.8:0.2"
msgid "1. Paṭhamamāravagga"
msgstr "1. About Māra"

#. </p><h1>
#. VAR: 8. Arahantasutta → arahā (pts1)
msgctxt "sn23.8:0.3"
msgid "8. Arahantasutta"
msgstr "8. A Perfected One"

#. </h1></div><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc1"></a>
msgctxt "sn23.8:1.1"
msgid "Sāvatthinidānaṃ."
msgstr "At Sāvatthī."

msgctxt "sn23.8:1.2"
msgid "Ekamantaṃ nisinnaṃ kho āyasmantaṃ rādhaṃ bhagavā etadavoca:"
msgstr "When Venerable Rādha was seated to one side, the Buddha said to him:"

msgctxt "sn23.8:1.3"
msgid "“pañcime, rādha, upādānakkhandhā."
msgstr "“Rādha, there are these five grasping aggregates."

msgctxt "sn23.8:1.4"
msgid "Katame pañca?"
msgstr "What five?"

msgctxt "sn23.8:1.5"
msgid "Rūpupādānakkhandho … pe … viññāṇupādānakkhandho."
msgstr ""
"The grasping aggregates of form, feeling, perception, choices, and "
"consciousness."

msgctxt "sn23.8:1.6"
msgid ""
"Yato kho, rādha, bhikkhu imesaṃ pañcannaṃ upādānakkhandhānaṃ samudayañca "
"atthaṅgamañca assādañca ādīnavañca nissaraṇañca yathābhūtaṃ viditvā "
"anupādāvimutto hoti—"
msgstr ""
"A mendicant comes to be freed by not grasping after truly understanding "
"these five grasping aggregates’ origin, ending, gratification, drawback, and "
"escape."

msgctxt "sn23.8:1.7"
msgid ""
"ayaṃ vuccati, rādha, bhikkhu arahaṃ khīṇāsavo vusitavā katakaraṇīyo "
"ohitabhāro anuppattasadattho parikkhīṇabhavasaṃyojano sammadaññāvimutto”ti."
msgstr ""
"Such a mendicant is called a perfected one, with defilements ended, who has "
"completed the spiritual journey, done what had to be done, laid down the "
"burden, achieved their own true goal, utterly ended the fetters of rebirth, "
"and is rightly freed through enlightenment.”"

#. </p><p class="endsection">
msgctxt "sn23.8:1.8"
msgid "Aṭṭhamaṃ."
msgstr ""
